article.headline: Boise State 72, Louisiana Tech 64
article.story: RUSTON, La. (AP) -- Aaron Haynes scored 25 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Boise State to a 72-64 victory over Louisiana Tech on Saturday night. Haynes had eight field goals in 19 tries and went 9-of-15 from the foul line to help give the Broncos (19-8, 11-6 Western Athletic Conference) their fifth consecutive win and eighth over their past nine games. Bryan Defares added 15 points for Boise State, while Coby Karl scored 13 points and Booker Nabors 10. Tech (13-13, 7-9), which has lost back-to-back games at home for the first time in over a year, got a career-high 24 points from Corey Dean along with 13 from reserve forward Barry Thompson. Boise State led in rebounding 43-41. The score was tied at 29 at halftime. <
